Text.SourceString: Huh? <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’m <NPCName>Dippa</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Huh? <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’m <NPCName>Dippa</>.

Text.SourceString: Oh, a corporate employee?//And now you’re a farmer. What a twist, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, a corporate employee?//And now you’re a farmer. What a twist, huh?

Text.SourceString: Hey, thanks for clearing up debris in the forest. I saw you’d done it a couple of times when I went there to paint.//I like to chill there sometimes, but I don’t have any farming tools, so I appreciate your doing that.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, thanks for clearing up debris in the forest. I saw you’d done it a couple of times when I went there to paint.//I like to chill there sometimes, but I don’t have any farming tools, so I appreciate your doing that.

Text.SourceString: How do you avoid getting bitten by bugs when you’re clearing land?
Text.LocalizedString: How do you avoid getting bitten by bugs when you’re clearing land?

Text.SourceString: How do you avoid getting bitten by bugs when you’re clearing land?
Text.LocalizedString: How do you avoid getting bitten by bugs when you’re clearing land?

Text.SourceString: You never know when inspiration might come. It could be now…//…or an hour from now, or even tonight, when you’re about to fall asleep.
Text.LocalizedString: You never know when inspiration might come. It could be now…//…or an hour from now, or even tonight, when you’re about to fall asleep.

Text.SourceString: That’s the beauty of art, isn’t it? So unpredictable.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s the beauty of art, isn’t it? So unpredictable.

Text.SourceString: Many painters are only appreciated after their tragic death.//<portrait=concerned>Makes you think, doesn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Many painters are only appreciated after their tragic death.//<portrait=concerned>Makes you think, doesn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I’m not a fan of night skies.//The darkness and silence only make me feel sadness and sorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a fan of night skies.//The darkness and silence only make me feel sadness and sorrow.

Text.SourceString: I try to paint something that lifts my mood…unless I’m in the mood for feeling sad.//Does that make sense?
Text.LocalizedString: I try to paint something that lifts my mood…unless I’m in the mood for feeling sad.//Does that make sense?

Text.SourceString: Fruit and wildlife inspire me. They’re so pure and free.
Text.LocalizedString: Fruit and wildlife inspire me. They’re so pure and free.

Text.SourceString: Who’s to say mangoes and jackfruit aren’t sentient?//We tend to assume too much, when in reality, we know so little.
Text.LocalizedString: Who’s to say mangoes and jackfruit aren’t sentient?//We tend to assume too much, when in reality, we know so little.

Text.SourceString: We don’t know everything.//Do <Italic>you</> know everything?
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t know everything.//Do <Italic>you</> know everything?

Text.SourceString: Besides painting on canvas, I collect rocks and paint on them.//<portrait=happy>They’re free. Good for my wallet.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides painting on canvas, I collect rocks and paint on them.//<portrait=happy>They’re free. Good for my wallet.

Text.SourceString: Meditating first thing in the morning helps me map out my day.//You gotta know what you want from the day in order to get it done, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Meditating first thing in the morning helps me map out my day.//You gotta know what you want from the day in order to get it done, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Some days, though, small things seem like such a chore.
Text.LocalizedString: Some days, though, small things seem like such a chore.

Text.SourceString: Town life isn’t for me. Socializing is too exhausting.
Text.LocalizedString: Town life isn’t for me. Socializing is too exhausting.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll avoid Fishensips this weekend.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll avoid Fishensips this weekend.

Text.SourceString: My brain feels sluggish. I could really use some inspiration right now. Or maybe a nice long walk in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: My brain feels sluggish. I could really use some inspiration right now. Or maybe a nice long walk in the rain.

Text.SourceString: My brain feels sluggish. I could really use some inspiration right now. Or maybe a nice long walk in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: My brain feels sluggish. I could really use some inspiration right now. Or maybe a nice long walk in the rain.

Text.SourceString: A nice long walk in the rain is all I need sometimes.//You too, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: A nice long walk in the rain is all I need sometimes.//You too, huh?

Text.SourceString: A nice long walk in the rain is all I need sometimes.//You too, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: A nice long walk in the rain is all I need sometimes.//You too, huh?

Text.SourceString: My brain feels sluggish. I could really use some inspiration right now. Or maybe a nice long walk in the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: My brain feels sluggish. I could really use some inspiration right now. Or maybe a nice long walk in the snow.

Text.SourceString: Me? Expressionless?//Nonsense.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? Expressionless?//Nonsense.

Text.SourceString: I’m plenty expressive. I’m smiling right now.//Can’t you see my excitement?//Yes, that’s a joke.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m plenty expressive. I’m smiling right now.//Can’t you see my excitement?//Yes, that’s a joke.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever kind of feel like you miss your old self sometimes?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever kind of feel like you miss your old self sometimes?

Text.SourceString: It’s okay to feel that way, I think.//<portrait=concerned>I miss my performing days all the time. That’s normal, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s okay to feel that way, I think.//<portrait=concerned>I miss my performing days all the time. That’s normal, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Back in the day, my hair had to be a natural color. You know, it was a job requirement.//They didn’t let us dye our hair unusual colors. Didn’t want to attract attention, they said.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in the day, my hair had to be a natural color. You know, it was a job requirement.//They didn’t let us dye our hair unusual colors. Didn’t want to attract attention, they said.

Text.SourceString: I can do whatever I want to my hair now, and nobody cares.//I could dye it purple tomorrow, and it wouldn’t matter. It doesn’t make any difference, because I don’t perform anymore.//<portrait=concerned>Ugh…
Text.LocalizedString: I can do whatever I want to my hair now, and nobody cares.//I could dye it purple tomorrow, and it wouldn’t matter. It doesn’t make any difference, because I don’t perform anymore.//<portrait=concerned>Ugh…

Text.SourceString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?//<portrait=happy>No offense. You have snow in your eyelashes.
Text.LocalizedString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?//<portrait=happy>No offense. You have snow in your eyelashes.

Text.SourceString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?//<portrait=happy>No offense.
Text.LocalizedString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?//<portrait=happy>No offense.

Text.SourceString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?//<portrait=happy>No offense. You have sand in your eyelashes.//<portrait=annoyed>How did you get sand in your <Italic>eyelashes</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?//<portrait=happy>No offense. You have sand in your eyelashes.//<portrait=annoyed>How did you get sand in your <Italic>eyelashes</>?

Text.SourceString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?/<portrait=happy>No offense. You have mud in your eyelashes.//<portrait=annoyed>Wait – is that <Italic>really</> mud in your eyelashes? How?
Text.LocalizedString: Bit of a mess, aren’t you?/<portrait=happy>No offense. You have mud in your eyelashes.//<portrait=annoyed>Wait – is that <Italic>really</> mud in your eyelashes? How?

Text.SourceString: You can get some of my paintings at Socket Electronics.//<NPCName>Luke</> has some in his store.
Text.LocalizedString: You can get some of my paintings at Socket Electronics.//<NPCName>Luke</> has some in his store.

Text.SourceString: Not everyone can follow their passion. And you know what? That’s okay.
Text.LocalizedString: Not everyone can follow their passion. And you know what? That’s okay.

Text.SourceString: Anyone who goes through a life-changing event knows that. Life goes on.//<portrait=concerned>There are other things, believe it or not. There are always other things in life.
Text.LocalizedString: Anyone who goes through a life-changing event knows that. Life goes on.//<portrait=concerned>There are other things, believe it or not. There are always other things in life.

Text.SourceString: Reruns are the best. You know precisely what you’re going to get, and you already know whether or not it’s good!//A total time saver.
Text.LocalizedString: Reruns are the best. You know precisely what you’re going to get, and you already know whether or not it’s good!//A total time saver.

Text.SourceString: I said it’s a total time saver. Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: I said it’s a total time saver. Humph.

Text.SourceString: Why do I feel like my creativity just isn’t flowing if I’m not in some sort of… Never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Why do I feel like my creativity just isn’t flowing if I’m not in some sort of… Never mind.

Text.SourceString: I hate self-doubt. It kills the fun.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate self-doubt. It kills the fun.

Text.SourceString: I hate drinking. The alcohol smell is the worst.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate drinking. The alcohol smell is the worst.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ben</> supplies me with out-of-season items sometimes. He’s strangely resourceful.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ben</> supplies me with out-of-season items sometimes. He’s strangely resourceful.

Text.SourceString: I do wonder where he gets his stuff.//<portrait=normal>Some of his things are great. He has nice seeds too. Better than <NPCName>Sam</>’s, I’d say.
Text.LocalizedString: I do wonder where he gets his stuff.//<portrait=normal>Some of his things are great. He has nice seeds too. Better than <NPCName>Sam</>’s, I’d say.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Emma</> insists on shopping at <NPCName>Sam</>’s for seeds. Beats me why.//<NPCName>Ben</> has good seeds too. Why not buy from him? Besides, he owes a lot to the taco truck. I might be able to get some for free.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Emma</> insists on shopping at <NPCName>Sam</>’s for seeds. Beats me why.//<NPCName>Ben</> has good seeds too. Why not buy from him? Besides, he owes a lot to the taco truck. I might be able to get some for free.

Text.SourceString: But hey, happy wife, happy life.
Text.LocalizedString: But hey, happy wife, happy life.

Text.SourceString: I miss performing.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss performing.

Text.SourceString: Now I can’t even take <NPCName>Emma</> to a performance without being a bummer about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Now I can’t even take <NPCName>Emma</> to a performance without being a bummer about it.

Text.SourceString: Farming isn’t something I could do, unfortunately. No more physical work for me.//I did enough in my youth to last the rest of my life. Now I paint, for crying out loud.
Text.LocalizedString: Farming isn’t something I could do, unfortunately. No more physical work for me.//I did enough in my youth to last the rest of my life. Now I paint, for crying out loud.

Text.SourceString: Me? I used to do gymnastics five days a week. Now I walk for exercise.//Life is funny that way.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? I used to do gymnastics five days a week. Now I walk for exercise.//Life is funny that way.

Text.SourceString: Walked past a bunch of kids going to school this morning. I see them, and I see hope.//I don’t know what I’m hoping exactly, but it makes it seem like the world isn’t as dark as it feels, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Walked past a bunch of kids going to school this morning. I see them, and I see hope.//I don’t know what I’m hoping exactly, but it makes it seem like the world isn’t as dark as it feels, you know?

Text.SourceString: My week has been good. What’s up, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: My week has been good. What’s up, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Started my day off with some hash browns and hot coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: Started my day off with some hash browns and hot coffee.

Text.SourceString: A little sip from an oasis of inspiration, I call it. Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: A little sip from an oasis of inspiration, I call it. Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: Pufferfish? Oh, I don’t care about things like that.//They own the place, so they’re free to use it however they like.
Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish? Oh, I don’t care about things like that.//They own the place, so they’re free to use it however they like.

Text.SourceString: I could use a nice big jar of fresh jam right now.//Strawberry jam. I should plant strawberries in my garden. They’re in season.
Text.LocalizedString: I could use a nice big jar of fresh jam right now.//Strawberry jam. I should plant strawberries in my garden. They’re in season.

Text.SourceString: Some of my paintings were painted in tears, so I hope when people look at them, they get the same feeling.//They don’t have to be sad tears. They could be happy ones, like the feeling of a new beginning in Spring after a long Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of my paintings were painted in tears, so I hope when people look at them, they get the same feeling.//They don’t have to be sad tears. They could be happy ones, like the feeling of a new beginning in Spring after a long Winter.

Text.SourceString: An artist should never be afraid to show emotion.//I try very hard to engage with my feelings before creating art.
Text.LocalizedString: An artist should never be afraid to show emotion.//I try very hard to engage with my feelings before creating art.

Text.SourceString: I like to magnify my feelings and emotions, then I get to work and pour them into the canvas.//That’s why I dread making dark paintings…
Text.LocalizedString: I like to magnify my feelings and emotions, then I get to work and pour them into the canvas.//That’s why I dread making dark paintings…

Text.SourceString: Some of my best work is from my dark days. It just seems easier to create when I’m in the depths.//It’s hard to do in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of my best work is from my dark days. It just seems easier to create when I’m in the depths.//It’s hard to do in Summer.

Text.SourceString: The hardest thing for me to paint is sadness. Yet those paintings turn out the best.//<portrait=happy>Isn’t the universe funny? The games she plays!
Text.LocalizedString: The hardest thing for me to paint is sadness. Yet those paintings turn out the best.//<portrait=happy>Isn’t the universe funny? The games she plays!

Text.SourceString: A good bout of emotion can be addictive. It’s my sole source of inspiration.//Without it, life is boring, and boring is no way to live.
Text.LocalizedString: A good bout of emotion can be addictive. It’s my sole source of inspiration.//Without it, life is boring, and boring is no way to live.

Text.SourceString: Our garden is lush this Summer. It feels good to eat food we grew ourselves.
Text.LocalizedString: Our garden is lush this Summer. It feels good to eat food we grew ourselves.

Text.SourceString: I took some sand from the beach the other day and used it in my latest painting.//It seems fitting, you know. It <Italic>is</> Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I took some sand from the beach the other day and used it in my latest painting.//It seems fitting, you know. It <Italic>is</> Summer.

Text.SourceString: Gah… Sunshine.//<portrait=annoyed>I hate it.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah… Sunshine.//<portrait=annoyed>I hate it.

Text.SourceString: Oh my!//If somebody tells me to have a great day one more time…
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my!//If somebody tells me to have a great day one more time…

Text.SourceString: Oops, sorry. I think I’m having a bad day… If you’ll excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: Oops, sorry. I think I’m having a bad day… If you’ll excuse me.

Text.SourceString: Gah… Another festival is coming up. It’s exhausting to go to so many community activities.//I’d rather stay at home, but I know <NPCName>Emma</> wants to go.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah… Another festival is coming up. It’s exhausting to go to so many community activities.//I’d rather stay at home, but I know <NPCName>Emma</> wants to go.

Text.SourceString: Well, at least there’ll be free mooncakes.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, at least there’ll be free mooncakes.

Text.SourceString: I painted falling leaves the other day. It turned out okay, but I’m not satisfied.
Text.LocalizedString: I painted falling leaves the other day. It turned out okay, but I’m not satisfied.

Text.SourceString: It’s generic and bland. It’s missing something, that’s for sure.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s generic and bland. It’s missing something, that’s for sure.

Text.SourceString: I really don’t want to walk in the snow.//My boots get all cold and soggy. Gah!
Text.LocalizedString: I really don’t want to walk in the snow.//My boots get all cold and soggy. Gah!

Text.SourceString: I hope you have a fireplace in your cabin for this kind of weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you have a fireplace in your cabin for this kind of weather.

Text.SourceString: All our crops died. It’s too cold, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: All our crops died. It’s too cold, I think.

Text.SourceString: I could use a nice long walk right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I could use a nice long walk right now.

Text.SourceString: I want to admire the town covered in snow before it all melts.
Text.LocalizedString: I want to admire the town covered in snow before it all melts.

Text.SourceString: Are you looking for something?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking for something?

Text.SourceString: There isn’t much for me to do when it rains, so I usually catch up on my reading here.
Text.LocalizedString: There isn’t much for me to do when it rains, so I usually catch up on my reading here.

Text.SourceString: There isn’t much for me to do when it rains, so I figured I’d help <NPCName>Luke</> with his display.
Text.LocalizedString: There isn’t much for me to do when it rains, so I figured I’d help <NPCName>Luke</> with his display.

Text.SourceString: Today's so gloomy.
Text.LocalizedString: Today's so gloomy.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna get muddy but maybe muddy is good sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna get muddy but maybe muddy is good sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I really have to go.
Text.LocalizedString: I really have to go.

Text.SourceString: There isn’t much for me to do when it storms, so I usually catch up on my reading here.
Text.LocalizedString: There isn’t much for me to do when it storms, so I usually catch up on my reading here.

Text.SourceString: There isn’t much for me to do when it storms, so I figured I’d help <NPCName>Luke</> with his display.
Text.LocalizedString: There isn’t much for me to do when it storms, so I figured I’d help <NPCName>Luke</> with his display.

Text.SourceString: Today's so gloomy.
Text.LocalizedString: Today's so gloomy.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna get muddy but maybe muddy is good sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna get muddy but maybe muddy is good sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Go home, <PlayerName>$player</>. It isn’t safe to wander around in the dark during a storm like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Go home, <PlayerName>$player</>. It isn’t safe to wander around in the dark during a storm like this.

Text.SourceString: Do you have one of those massive heaters we could borrow?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have one of those massive heaters we could borrow?

Text.SourceString: Anything can be an inspiration. Flowers, animals… Life events.
Text.LocalizedString: Anything can be an inspiration. Flowers, animals… Life events.

Text.SourceString: My fear is I might run out of inspiration someday. Then what would I do with myself?
Text.LocalizedString: My fear is I might run out of inspiration someday. Then what would I do with myself?

Text.SourceString: I like painting inanimate objects.//The challenge of bringing them to life grounds me.
Text.LocalizedString: I like painting inanimate objects.//The challenge of bringing them to life grounds me.

Text.SourceString: Some days, I get caught up in an idea, and all of a sudden, it’s nighttime.
Text.LocalizedString: Some days, I get caught up in an idea, and all of a sudden, it’s nighttime.

Text.SourceString: I’m using my favorite brush to paint today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m using my favorite brush to paint today.

Text.SourceString: It makes me happy.//<portrait=happy>Can’t you tell?
Text.LocalizedString: It makes me happy.//<portrait=happy>Can’t you tell?

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I use wool or fresh flowers instead of a brush. It’s fun to change things up.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I use wool or fresh flowers instead of a brush. It’s fun to change things up.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… How do you know when a painting is finished?//<portrait=happy>You don’t. You let your instinct decide.//<portrait=normal>If it’s finished, then it’ll feel finished. Until then, keep painting.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… How do you know when a painting is finished?//<portrait=happy>You don’t. You let your instinct decide.//<portrait=normal>If it’s finished, then it’ll feel finished. Until then, keep painting.

Text.SourceString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Emma</>, she should be by the school somewhere.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Emma</>, she should be by the school somewhere.

Text.SourceString: There are birds’ nests everywhere. I think it’s a sign.
Text.LocalizedString: There are birds’ nests everywhere. I think it’s a sign.

Text.SourceString: I need to paint them. Nature chose birds’ nests as my next subject.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to paint them. Nature chose birds’ nests as my next subject.

Text.SourceString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Emma</>, she should be in the woodland somewhere.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Emma</>, she should be in the woodland somewhere.

Text.SourceString: Our cottage is pretty small, huh?//I don’t know what we’d do if we decided to get a pet.
Text.LocalizedString: Our cottage is pretty small, huh?//I don’t know what we’d do if we decided to get a pet.

Text.SourceString: If I only had my old job back, I’d be able to afford more than this.
Text.LocalizedString: If I only had my old job back, I’d be able to afford more than this.

Text.SourceString: Ah, those pictures are from my performing days. They’re covered with dust now.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, those pictures are from my performing days. They’re covered with dust now.

Text.SourceString: I’m on a roll right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m on a roll right now.

Text.SourceString: I feel full of creativity and inspiration.//<portrait=happy>Nature spoke to me today.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel full of creativity and inspiration.//<portrait=happy>Nature spoke to me today.

Text.SourceString: I don’t give pointers. You should paint you.//Get drenched in emotion. Be honest with yourself.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t give pointers. You should paint you.//Get drenched in emotion. Be honest with yourself.

Text.SourceString: Only then can you let yourself go on the canvas.//Until then, I’m afraid your paintings will be empty.
Text.LocalizedString: Only then can you let yourself go on the canvas.//Until then, I’m afraid your paintings will be empty.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see you in such good spirits, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see you in such good spirits, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I suppose one of us should be, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose one of us should be, huh?

Text.SourceString: By the way, <NPCName>Sam</> was <NPCName>Emma’s</> old boss. He was the one who helped her with the taco truck in the beginning.//<portrait=happy>He gave her free groceries until she could support herself with the business.
Text.LocalizedString: By the way, <NPCName>Sam</> was <NPCName>Emma’s</> old boss. He was the one who helped her with the taco truck in the beginning.//<portrait=happy>He gave her free groceries until she could support herself with the business.

Text.SourceString: She’s very grateful to them… Oh, <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</>, I mean.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s very grateful to them… Oh, <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</>, I mean.

Text.SourceString: Ugh… My back is killing me.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh… My back is killing me.

Text.SourceString: Hobbies? Uh… I like to paint.//That’s about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Hobbies? Uh… I like to paint.//That’s about it.

Text.SourceString: You ever think about how your life could have gone if you hadn’t made some little mistake?
Text.LocalizedString: You ever think about how your life could have gone if you hadn’t made some little mistake?

Text.SourceString: Don’t. Dwelling on that stuff will kill your spirit.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t. Dwelling on that stuff will kill your spirit.

Text.SourceString: As a kid, I loved to paint. It fell by the wayside when I…went down another career path.
Text.LocalizedString: As a kid, I loved to paint. It fell by the wayside when I…went down another career path.

Text.SourceString: But I’m back at it. Didn’t have much of a choice.
Text.LocalizedString: But I’m back at it. Didn’t have much of a choice.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could say other people’s opinions don’t bother me. But everyone needs validation.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could say other people’s opinions don’t bother me. But everyone needs validation.

Text.SourceString: I tried meditating, but it didn’t go well. Mindfulness doesn’t stop the back pain.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried meditating, but it didn’t go well. Mindfulness doesn’t stop the back pain.

Text.SourceString: You’re right. I guess it works for some people. Not me, though.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re right. I guess it works for some people. Not me, though.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever had <NPCName>Emma’s</> tacos?//They’re killer.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever had <NPCName>Emma’s</> tacos?//They’re killer.

Text.SourceString: You ever listen to The Luwaks? Punk band.//Love ’em. Give their latest album a listen if you have the time.
Text.LocalizedString: You ever listen to The Luwaks? Punk band.//Love ’em. Give their latest album a listen if you have the time.

Text.SourceString: You doing okay? Good.
Text.LocalizedString: You doing okay? Good.

Text.SourceString: Where are you from, anyway? Never asked.//I mean where in Pokyo City did you live?
Text.LocalizedString: Where are you from, anyway? Never asked.//I mean where in Pokyo City did you live?

Text.SourceString: The what? Ah! Interesting. I’ve been a few times.//<portrait=happy>It’s a bit much for me at my age.
Text.LocalizedString: The what? Ah! Interesting. I’ve been a few times.//<portrait=happy>It’s a bit much for me at my age.

Text.SourceString: So, uh, you ever do art, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: So, uh, you ever do art, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Meh. It’s a skill. Anyone can learn if they’re persistent enough.
Text.LocalizedString: Meh. It’s a skill. Anyone can learn if they’re persistent enough.

Special.SourceString: I can’t even draw a stick figure!
Special.LocalizedString: I can’t even draw a stick figure!

Text.SourceString: Good. It’s good for you. Self-expression and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Good. It’s good for you. Self-expression and stuff.

Text.SourceString: Really? You’ll have to show me your work sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: Really? You’ll have to show me your work sometime.

Text.SourceString: Rain is good for your crops, right?//Neat.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain is good for your crops, right?//Neat.

Text.SourceString: No need to water my garden today.
Text.LocalizedString: No need to water my garden today.

Text.SourceString: Rain is good for your crops, right?//Neat.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain is good for your crops, right?//Neat.

Text.SourceString: No need to water my garden today.
Text.LocalizedString: No need to water my garden today.

Text.SourceString: One time, I was doing this huge outdoor painting project, and it started pouring.//I nearly had a panic attack.
Text.LocalizedString: One time, I was doing this huge outdoor painting project, and it started pouring.//I nearly had a panic attack.

Text.SourceString: But the rain actually washed away parts of it I hated.//The rest I could fix easily.//<portrait=happy>Happy accident. My favorite artist taught me that.
Text.LocalizedString: But the rain actually washed away parts of it I hated.//The rest I could fix easily.//<portrait=happy>Happy accident. My favorite artist taught me that.

Text.SourceString: It sure is snowing. Glad you don’t have to farm in this weather.//But then, what <Italic>are</> you gonna do?
Text.LocalizedString: It sure is snowing. Glad you don’t have to farm in this weather.//But then, what <Italic>are</> you gonna do?

Text.SourceString: The snow makes me look like I have bad dandruff.//<portrait=normal>See any on my hair?
Text.LocalizedString: The snow makes me look like I have bad dandruff.//<portrait=normal>See any on my hair?

Text.SourceString: The snow is pretty.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is pretty.

Text.SourceString: It’s wild to me that this island gets snow in Winter when the Summers get so dang hot.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s wild to me that this island gets snow in Winter when the Summers get so dang hot.

Text.SourceString: Nature sells. But it’s also comforting, in a way.
Text.LocalizedString: Nature sells. But it’s also comforting, in a way.

Text.SourceString: The lake has seen better days, but the ocean is even worse.
Text.LocalizedString: The lake has seen better days, but the ocean is even worse.

Text.SourceString: I actually don’t care if what I paint here sells or not. It makes me happy.
Text.LocalizedString: I actually don’t care if what I paint here sells or not. It makes me happy.

Text.SourceString: Want to watch TV with me? I love this show.
Text.LocalizedString: Want to watch TV with me? I love this show.

Text.SourceString: I like this spot. It has a nice view.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this spot. It has a nice view.

Text.SourceString: I try to look closely when I paint here. The closer I look, the more unusual my paintings get.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to look closely when I paint here. The closer I look, the more unusual my paintings get.

Text.SourceString: This is a nice spot for painting people.
Text.LocalizedString: This is a nice spot for painting people.

Text.SourceString: Could you move a little? You’re in the way.
Text.LocalizedString: Could you move a little? You’re in the way.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know why, but I woke up thinking about the night I broke my back.//What a bummer way to start the day.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know why, but I woke up thinking about the night I broke my back.//What a bummer way to start the day.

Text.SourceString: Everything went great at the rehearsal. Then I fell doing an aerial stunt. Don’t remember much after that.//The next thing I knew, I woke up in a hospital.
Text.LocalizedString: Everything went great at the rehearsal. Then I fell doing an aerial stunt. Don’t remember much after that.//The next thing I knew, I woke up in a hospital.

Text.SourceString: I hate jolly people.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate jolly people.

Text.SourceString: Did I say hate? I meant dislike.//Summer’s full of them.
Text.LocalizedString: Did I say hate? I meant dislike.//Summer’s full of them.

Text.SourceString: People are opinionated, aren’t they?//Gotta stop listening to people, <PlayerName>$player</>. If we listened to every single thing everybody said, it would only drive us mad.
Text.LocalizedString: People are opinionated, aren’t they?//Gotta stop listening to people, <PlayerName>$player</>. If we listened to every single thing everybody said, it would only drive us mad.

Text.SourceString: I avoid people altogether.//I’m better off listening to my own voice inside my head.
Text.LocalizedString: I avoid people altogether.//I’m better off listening to my own voice inside my head.

Text.SourceString: Inspiration is hard to come by. When it finally strikes, you could end up getting lost.//<portrait=happy>You could stay too long and forget the way back home.
Text.LocalizedString: Inspiration is hard to come by. When it finally strikes, you could end up getting lost.//<portrait=happy>You could stay too long and forget the way back home.

Text.SourceString: I do commissions here and there. I don’t encourage them, though. I don’t like being told what I should paint.
Text.LocalizedString: I do commissions here and there. I don’t encourage them, though. I don’t like being told what I should paint.

Text.SourceString: But some customers are willing to pay so much I can’t say no.
Text.LocalizedString: But some customers are willing to pay so much I can’t say no.

Text.SourceString: I’ve gotten plenty of commissions from <NPCName>Bree</>. She seems to like my work, but she likes exclusivity.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, and she’s sent some of my paintings to her family too, I believe.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve gotten plenty of commissions from <NPCName>Bree</>. She seems to like my work, but she likes exclusivity.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, and she’s sent some of my paintings to her family too, I believe.

Text.SourceString: She also made me sign one of those documents about the original work.//I can’t make copies and all that. Who cares, really?
Text.LocalizedString: She also made me sign one of those documents about the original work.//I can’t make copies and all that. Who cares, really?

Text.SourceString: I can always tell when you’re nearby. You smell of fresh flowers.//Like the kind I find near the lake.//I don’t know the names. I’m not too familiar with plants.
Text.LocalizedString: I can always tell when you’re nearby. You smell of fresh flowers.//Like the kind I find near the lake.//I don’t know the names. I’m not too familiar with plants.

Text.SourceString: I probably smell like paint, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I probably smell like paint, right?

Text.SourceString: Saying things out loud helps me control my thoughts.//That’s a good thing, because sometimes there are so many bad ones bubbling in my head.//I wish I’d known I could do that earlier.
Text.LocalizedString: Saying things out loud helps me control my thoughts.//That’s a good thing, because sometimes there are so many bad ones bubbling in my head.//I wish I’d known I could do that earlier.

Text.SourceString: I think I probably knew about it, but I was just too hard-headed to believe it.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I probably knew about it, but I was just too hard-headed to believe it.

Text.SourceString: I wasn’t a professional acrobat long enough before I got injured.//I didn’t have much savings.
Text.LocalizedString: I wasn’t a professional acrobat long enough before I got injured.//I didn’t have much savings.

Text.SourceString: With the hospital bill, my savings were gone, just like that.//I liked the job, so I guess money didn’t matter at the time.
Text.LocalizedString: With the hospital bill, my savings were gone, just like that.//I liked the job, so I guess money didn’t matter at the time.

Text.SourceString: I forgot it takes a while for strawberries to grow.//I planted several last week, but now they’re all withered.
Text.LocalizedString: I forgot it takes a while for strawberries to grow.//I planted several last week, but now they’re all withered.

Text.SourceString: We’re planting hot peppers this Summer.//The seeds are pretty cheap, and the plants last till Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re planting hot peppers this Summer.//The seeds are pretty cheap, and the plants last till Winter.

Text.SourceString: The hot peppers we planted in Summer grew great.//They saved us a lot of money. No need to buy more seeds.//They grew and grew and grew. No withering for them.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot peppers we planted in Summer grew great.//They saved us a lot of money. No need to buy more seeds.//They grew and grew and grew. No withering for them.

Text.SourceString: I should paint pumpkins. What do you think?//I don’t really feel like it, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I should paint pumpkins. What do you think?//I don’t really feel like it, though.

Text.SourceString: I just got back from <NpcName>Ben’s</> place.//Took some of my paintings there. He said he’d put them in his caravan and see if anyone’s interested in buying while he’s traveling.
Text.LocalizedString: I just got back from <NpcName>Ben’s</> place.//Took some of my paintings there. He said he’d put them in his caravan and see if anyone’s interested in buying while he’s traveling.

Text.SourceString: I asked <NpcName>Ben</> to take some of my paintings on his travels.//He sold a couple last Fall.//I like that guy.
Text.LocalizedString: I asked <NpcName>Ben</> to take some of my paintings on his travels.//He sold a couple last Fall.//I like that guy.

Text.SourceString: It’s not a bad idea, living in a mobile home.//<NpcName>Ben’s</> doing it, and he seems happy.//But it might be a <Italic>little</> cold when the snow is raging like it is now.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not a bad idea, living in a mobile home.//<NpcName>Ben’s</> doing it, and he seems happy.//But it might be a <Italic>little</> cold when the snow is raging like it is now.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever just bring things you find on your way to the Cherry Blossom Festival for the potluck?//Sometimes I do. Why not, right? They’re at their freshest, technically.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever just bring things you find on your way to the Cherry Blossom Festival for the potluck?//Sometimes I do. Why not, right? They’re at their freshest, technically.

Text.SourceString: I ran into the mayor the other day. He was chilling across the river, fishing.//That man sure likes fishing.
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into the mayor the other day. He was chilling across the river, fishing.//That man sure likes fishing.

Text.SourceString: I spotted him near Fishensips too – fishing!//Maybe he’s trying to catch Spring fish. We’ll never know.
Text.LocalizedString: I spotted him near Fishensips too – fishing!//Maybe he’s trying to catch Spring fish. We’ll never know.

Text.SourceString: Living in the middle of nowhere has its downsides.//Just yesterday, I think I saw a massive bear. A flute-playing bear walking past the river.
Text.LocalizedString: Living in the middle of nowhere has its downsides.//Just yesterday, I think I saw a massive bear. A flute-playing bear walking past the river.

Text.SourceString: I peeked from the window.//Scary stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I peeked from the window.//Scary stuff.

Text.SourceString: Maybe someday, if I paint enough happy things, I’ll be able to let go of some bad things.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe someday, if I paint enough happy things, I’ll be able to let go of some bad things.

Text.SourceString: Fall windows are good subject to paint.//A peek into an empty, warm room.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall windows are good subject to paint.//A peek into an empty, warm room.

Text.SourceString: Almost stepped on a dog this morning. It was taking a nap in a pile of leaves.//<NpcName>Paul’s</> dog, I think. Not so sure. The dog ran away really fast.
Text.LocalizedString: Almost stepped on a dog this morning. It was taking a nap in a pile of leaves.//<NpcName>Paul’s</> dog, I think. Not so sure. The dog ran away really fast.

Text.SourceString: Gave me a heart attack. Good grief!
Text.LocalizedString: Gave me a heart attack. Good grief!

Text.SourceString: We’ve been cranking up the heat this Winter.//I’m not looking forward to the electric bill.
Text.LocalizedString: We’ve been cranking up the heat this Winter.//I’m not looking forward to the electric bill.

Text.SourceString: I need to start shutting off the heater during the day.//Save on the electric bills.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to start shutting off the heater during the day.//Save on the electric bills.

Text.SourceString: I could use tea leaves and brew some tea for myself. Warm my body up.//<NpcName>Emma</> loves her green tea too.
Text.LocalizedString: I could use tea leaves and brew some tea for myself. Warm my body up.//<NpcName>Emma</> loves her green tea too.

Text.SourceString: Alcohol keeps your body warm, but I don’t drink. I hate alcohol.
Text.LocalizedString: Alcohol keeps your body warm, but I don’t drink. I hate alcohol.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Emma</> drinks alcohol. You could gift her sake and stuff.//I don’t mind. I don’t have a problem with people drinking around me.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Emma</> drinks alcohol. You could gift her sake and stuff.//I don’t mind. I don’t have a problem with people drinking around me.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Luke</> told me he’s seen painted coats for sale, and people are <Italic>buying</>!//I suppose it <Italic>is</> Winter. The demand for coats is high.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Luke</> told me he’s seen painted coats for sale, and people are <Italic>buying</>!//I suppose it <Italic>is</> Winter. The demand for coats is high.

Text.SourceString: I should look into it. Would you buy a hand-painted coat?//How much would you pay?
Text.LocalizedString: I should look into it. Would you buy a hand-painted coat?//How much would you pay?

Text.SourceString: Bonsai are kind of neat. They seem easy to take care of.//I like them.
Text.LocalizedString: Bonsai are kind of neat. They seem easy to take care of.//I like them.

Text.SourceString: I checked out <NpcName>Lily’s</> bonsai garden this morning.//They’re all so pretty.
Text.LocalizedString: I checked out <NpcName>Lily’s</> bonsai garden this morning.//They’re all so pretty.

Text.SourceString: I’m tempted to create a bonsai garden. Maybe it could be across from our vegetable garden.//But it would be too much work.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m tempted to create a bonsai garden. Maybe it could be across from our vegetable garden.//But it would be too much work.

Text.SourceString: It would be too much to keep up with that <Italic>and</> the vegetable garden. Gosh!//No, thank you! Recipe for back pain right there.
Text.LocalizedString: It would be too much to keep up with that <Italic>and</> the vegetable garden. Gosh!//No, thank you! Recipe for back pain right there.

Text.SourceString: The neighbors invited us for a volleyball game.//Not about to show off my nonexistent volleyball skills literally during the busiest time of year at the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: The neighbors invited us for a volleyball game.//Not about to show off my nonexistent volleyball skills literally during the busiest time of year at the beach.

Text.SourceString: I’ve seen them play. They’re good!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve seen them play. They’re good!

Text.SourceString: Can’t wait for Spring. I miss morels already.
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t wait for Spring. I miss morels already.

Text.SourceString: It’s a little too cold for morels right now. Once the snow melts, they’ll grow.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a little too cold for morels right now. Once the snow melts, they’ll grow.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Emma</> is adorable. I know she doesn’t like painting much. She’d rather garden.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Emma</> is adorable. I know she doesn’t like painting much. She’d rather garden.

Text.SourceString: She never said it, but I can tell. She gets frustrated easily when she gets things “wrong,” and yet she makes sure we paint together now and then.//I love her.
Text.LocalizedString: She never said it, but I can tell. She gets frustrated easily when she gets things “wrong,” and yet she makes sure we paint together now and then.//I love her.

Text.SourceString: We got a box of radishes yesterday from our neighbors. They must’ve had a bountiful harvest.//<portrait=happy>So kind of them.
Text.LocalizedString: We got a box of radishes yesterday from our neighbors. They must’ve had a bountiful harvest.//<portrait=happy>So kind of them.

Text.SourceString: I love radishes. They’re my favorite vegetable.//They’re great in tacos. Radishes and a bit of hot sauce!
Text.LocalizedString: I love radishes. They’re my favorite vegetable.//They’re great in tacos. Radishes and a bit of hot sauce!

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow is <NpcName>Emma’s</> birthday. I’m ready.//I filled a box with her favorite things. I can’t wait for her to open it.
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow is <NpcName>Emma’s</> birthday. I’m ready.//I filled a box with her favorite things. I can’t wait for her to open it.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Emma’s</> birthday was yesterday. We had a chill evening.//I made her a candlelit dinner, and we relaxed at home. She was happy, and that made me happy.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Emma’s</> birthday was yesterday. We had a chill evening.//I made her a candlelit dinner, and we relaxed at home. She was happy, and that made me happy.

Text.SourceString: Cats got inside the taco truck last week, and gosh, it was a mess!//Cat hair everywhere. Took us the whole day to clean it up.
Text.LocalizedString: Cats got inside the taco truck last week, and gosh, it was a mess!//Cat hair everywhere. Took us the whole day to clean it up.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Emma</> forgot to close the roof window. That’s where they must’ve gotten in.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Emma</> forgot to close the roof window. That’s where they must’ve gotten in.
